# Build-context exclusions for the Fly deploy.
#
# flyctl resolves .dockerignore next to the --dockerfile
# (apps/api/Dockerfile.fly), NOT the repo-root .dockerignore — so without
# this file a cold remote builder ships the ENTIRE monorepo (~900MB of
# node_modules + .git) over the wire every deploy, which is the ~6min
# "transferring context" stall. Everything excluded here is either
# regenerated inside the build (node_modules via `pnpm install`, dist via
# `pnpm build`, the prisma client via `prisma generate`) or irrelevant to
# it. Patterns are relative to the build context root (the repo root).
**/node_modules
.git
.github
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/coverage
*.log
.env
.env.*
.demo-logs
.demo-pids
.demo-urls
debug-*.png
debug-*.html
